column8: A pair of tough-skinned boots that change to meet the demands of the wearer.
Boots that allow the wearer to travel between the ether.
Teleports you to a target friendly building.
A simple wand used to channel magic energies.
Magi equipped with these boots are valued in battle.
A scepter of a wizard with demigod-like powers.
The fabled dagger used by the fastest assassin ever to walk the lands.
A powerful staff imbued with the strength of giants.
An old bottle that survived the ages.
The blade of a fallen king it allows you to move unseen and strike from the shadows.
A glowing jewel formed out of assorted parts that somehow fit together perfectly.
Allows you to manipulate others for good or evil.
A wicked weapon used in torturing political criminals.
While they increase the longevity of the wearer this boot is not particularly reliable.
A powerful shield that defends its wielder from even the most vicious of attacks.
Winged boots that grant omnipresence.
Contains the ashes of powerful demons.
A seemingly ordinary branch its ironlike qualities are bestowed upon the bearer.
When attuned by the moonlight and used together they become a very powerful combination.
The ring of the fallen Warlord Aquila continues to support armies in battle.
An eerie mask that is haunted with the malice of a fallen vampire.
A razor-sharp coat of mail.
The bracer is a common choice to toughen up defenses and increace longevity.
The bearer of this mighty axe gains the ability to cut down swaths of enemies at once.
A relic that enchants the bodies of those around it for swifter movement in times of crisis.
Fleet footwear increasing movement.
Preserved heart of an extinct monster. It bolsters the bearer's fortitude.
A blade forged from rare crystals. It seeks weak points in every armour.
One man's wine barrel bottom is another man's shield.
A weapon of incredible power that it is difficult for even the strongest of warriors to control.
You grow stronger just by holding it.
An axe made of reflective materials that causes confusion amongst enemy ranks.
Once this mask is worn it's bearer becomes an uncontrollable aggressive force.
Forged in the depths of the nether reaches this hellish mail provides an army with increased armour and attack speed.
Preserved through unknown magical means.
The powerful headpiece of a dead necromancer.
A busted old shield that seems to block more than it should.
Yasha is regarded as the swiftest weapon ever created.
The axe of a fallen gnome.
A feared weapon in the right hands.
Forage to survive on the battlefield.
Reveals invisible heroes.
Ring given as a reward to the greatest mages.
Gives sight of the surrounding area.
Only the mightiest and most experienced of warriors can wield the Butterfly.
Weapon of choice amongst brutes.
A circlet with faint whispers echoing about it.
A small gemstone attached to several chains.
A staff of magical powers passed down from the eldest mages.
A garnet rod constucted from the essence of a fire demon.
Instantly commits suicide on use.
A mysterious scepter passed down through the ages.
A hammer forged of pure mithril.
A perfectly formed amethyst that nourishes the body and mind when held.
This magical sphere once protected one of the most famous heroes in history.
A gem that grants heart to the bearer.
A ring that feeds on the sould of those around it.
A simple wand used to channel magic energies.
Thor's magical hammer made for him by the dwarves Brok and Eitri.
A mystical orb containing the essence of life.
The most guarded relic among the cult of Vyse. It is the most coveted weapon among magi.
Gives True Sight to the surrounding area.
A mystical carved stone that boosts the fervor of the holder.
Thick metal plates that protect the entire upper body. Avoid dropping on feet.
Gives the ability to see invisible units and wards.
A powerful staff used by a master warrior.
Said to have belonged to a goddess.
A divine weapon that causes damage and a bright burning effect lays waste to nearby enemies.
A powerful artifact of mysterious origin.
A ruby gemstone that has been passed down through generations of warrior kin.
A furred magic resistant headpiece that is feared by wizards.
Imbues the wielder with a ghostly presence.
A hammer forged for the gods themselves. Allows the user to harness the power of lightning.
A massive axe capable of tearing whole mountains down.
A powerful artifact created for wizards.
An enchanted blade that allows the user to cut straight into the enemy's soul.
A long blade imbued with time magic.
Extremely rare artifact guarded by the azure dragons.
Considered the holy grail of necromancy and demonology. A powerful malefic force is locked within its pages.
Studded leather gloves that add brute strength.
The lost blade of the Commander of the Abyss. This edge cuts into an enemy's soul.
A rather typical spear that can sometimes pierce through an enemy's armour when used to attack.
A magical salve that can quickly mend even the deepest of wounds.
Deceptively hidden as an ordinary quarterstaff. It is actually very powerful much like the Eldritch who originally possessed it.
One of the oldest weapons forged by the Demon-Smith Abzidian. It killed its maker when he tested its edge.
Clear water that enhances the ability to meditate.
A lesser wand that grows in power the longer it is used.
A medium weave of metal chains.
Jewlery that was once used to channel nether realm magic.
Light boots made from spider skin that tingles your senses.
This halberd moves with the speed of a smaller weapon allowing the bearer to win duels that a heavy edge would not.
A basic staff that allows you to strike quickly.
This ring is considered a good luck charm among the Gnomes.
The Immortal wass said to own a shield that protected him from death itself.
Creates a soothing aura that restores allies in battle.
Envenoms your vepon with the venom of a venoumous spider.
A necklace that allows you to anticipate enemy attacks.
A lesser wand that grows in power the longer it is used.
A shiny ring found beneath a fat halfling's corpse.
Enigmatic staff made of only the most expensive crystals.
The classic weapon of choice for knights. This blade is sturdy and reliable for slaying enemies.
So powerful it cannot have a single owner.
A valued accessory for improving vitality.
The headwear of corrupt magi.
A sword that can cut through armour. It's a commonly chosen first weapon for budding swordsmen.
A mask that drains the energy of those caught in its gaze.
An enchanted blade that allows the user to cut straight into the enemy's soul.
Capturing the magestic call of an eagle this mystical horn briings limitless dexterity to those who hear it.
A mask commonly used by mages and warlocks for various rituals.
Sange is an unusually accurate weapon seeking weak points automatically.
Immense power at the cost of your soul.
A pair of magical gloves that seems to render weapons weightless.
This robe corrupts the soul of the user but provides wisdom in return.
The damage of these small concealable blades should not be underestimated.
The bearer has no fear of combat.
A flickering blade of a ghastly nature. It is capable of dealing damage in both magical and physical planes.
A cloak made of a magical material that works to dispel any magic cast on it.
A beautiful sapphire mantle worn by generations of queens.
A lesser wand that grows in power the longer it is used.
A powerful shield that imbues the bearer with the strength of heroes past.
Allows invisibility for a short period of time.
A lesser wand that grows in power the longer it is used.
A tensile fabric often used for its light weight and ease of movement.
Atos the lord of Blight has his essence stored in this deceptively simple wand.
Grants invisibility to you or a targeted allied hero.
An ancient weapon that often turns the tides of war.
A glimmering ring that defends its bearer.
A lesser wand that grows in power the longer it is used.
An elegant circlet designed for human princesses.
Regain lost courage.
Considered the holy grail of necromancy and demonology. A powerful malefic force is locked within its pages.
The helmet of a legendary warrior who fell in battle.
This lapis gemstone is commonly added to the collection of wizards seeking to improve their presence in combat.
Considered the holy grail of necromancy and demonology. A powerful malefic force is locked within its pages.
Made from the milm of a long lost Furbolg vendor. It restored vitality of those who taste it.
A shared Tango. Increases health.
Creature that carries items to and from your base.
Fast flying creature that carries items to and from your base. Requires Animal Courier.
